[[File:Damaged armour detail.png|left|130px]]
'''Damaged armour''' is an item that can be found by digging at the [[digsite]], from the [[Fishing Trawler]] minigame, or from [[Thieving|pick-pocketing]] certain monsters (including [[Humans Against Monsters|H.A.M.]] members). It is also found in ogre coffins (see [[Ogre coffin key]]), and can be telegrabbed inside the [[Ranging Guild]]'s archery competition spot.

Players may also find damaged armours scattered throughout ''RuneScape'' in the form of scenery. However, these ones may not be picked up.

[[Members]] can repair it at an [[armour stand]] (55 [[construction]] required to build, but players could use others') in the [[workshop]] of a [[player-owned house]]. It will then become a platebody armour made from a random metal, although there is a significant chance of breaking it beyond repair. The most common armour produced this way is an [[Iron platebody]], though [[Bronze platebody|bronze]], [[Steel platebody|steel]], [[black platebody|black]] and [[mithril platebody|mithril]] are also possible. Successfully repairing a damaged armour gives 25 [[Smithing]] experience.

